    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Describes a series of dances performed at Native North American powwows. While the schedules and type of dances performed change based on the host nation, most powwows consist of a set of core dances: Traditional/Straight Dance, Grass Dance, Fancy Dance, Jingle Dress Dance, Fancy Shawl Dance, and intertribals.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
